 lives because none of my grandparents were alive when I was born, so I never had any grandparents.  Both my parents were political refugees from Hitler\rquote 
s Europe, although they met and married in England.  My mother was born in Germany.  Until the age of 16 she lived in Berlin, and her parents were quite prosperous, her father was a banker.  They then emigrated to Prague in 1936 \endash 
